                <note rend="inline" type="source">662.11241/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-12T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 12, 1926—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Your 72, April 9. Under Article 27 of recent treaty this Government accords
                    German career consular officers assigned United States privilege importing
                    effects and merchandise free of duty at any time. November 10, 1925, German
                    Embassy asked free entry mail package for Consul Lüders, attached Embassy,
                    citing Article 27 as ground for request. This and all subsequent similar
                    requests granted. Insist on full reciprocity for American Consular Officers
                    assigned Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
